#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:42
msgid "This is our selection for newcomers. These links are not commercial."
msgstr "這些是我們為初心者選擇的散布版。以下這些連結並非商業行銷。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:51
msgid "Debian is one of the oldest operating systems based on the Linux kernel. It has the reputation of being a very stable and secure GNU/Linux distribution which is backed by a well-organized community of developers and users. For this reason it is popular for use on personal computers as well as servers. Debian is also the basis for many other distributions, most notably Ubuntu."
msgstr "Debian 是以 Linux 核心為基礎的其中一個相當古老的散佈版。其被譽為非常穩定且安全的 GNU/Linux 散佈版，並有良好組織的開發者與使用者社群在背後支持。因此，它在個人電腦與伺服器上都很流行。Debian 也是許多其他散佈版的基礎，其中最著名的當屬 Ubuntu。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:52
msgid "We recommend this distribution if you are committed to freedom in your computing."
msgstr "倘若你致力於保有電腦運算的自由，那我們推薦這個散布版。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:79
msgid "Ubuntu is a GNU/Linux distribution based on Debian. The philosophy behind Ubuntu is that every computer user should be able to download and use their software free of charge, that anyone should be able to use their software in the language of their choice, and that anyone should be able to use all software regardless of disability. The result is an operating system that has excellent hardware support, is easy to use and pleasant on the eyes."
msgstr "Ubuntu 是一套以 Debian 為基礎的 GNU/Linux 散佈版。Ubuntu 背後的理念是，每個電腦使用者都應該要可以免費下載與使用他們的軟體，任何人都應該要可以選擇他們想要的語言來使用這些軟體，而且不管有沒有身心上的障礙都可以使用所有的軟體。而其結果是一套有著出色的硬體支援、易於使用且令人愉悅的作業系統。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:80
msgid "We recommend this friendly and complete distribution if you are looking for an easy way to try and step into GNU/Linux."
msgstr "如果你正在尋找一個嘗試及踏入 GNU/Linux 的簡單輕鬆之路，我們推薦這個友善且功能齊全的散布版。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:107
msgid "The distribution by the long-time prominent GNU/Linux developer company Red Hat. The default layout is similar to Debian, but there are differences in the chosen applications, install protocols and several technical elements. The Fedora developers are committed to innovation, which is reflected by incorporating new technologies early on, providing the latest in stable and robust, useful, and powerful free software."
msgstr "這個散佈版是由長期以來傑出的 GNU/Linux 開發者公司「Red Hat 紅帽」所開發的版本。 雖然預設的畫面配置接近 Debian，但預選的軟體、安裝方式以及其他技術性細節等與其不同。Fedora 開發者致力於創新，透過盡早加入新技術來體現，並提供穩定、可靠、好用且強大的最新自由軟體。"

#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:108
msgid "We recommend this distribution if you wish to learn more about the workings of a GNU/Linux system, security configuration, or work on software development."
msgstr "倘若你希望能學習 GNU/Linux 系統的工作原理、安全性設定，或者是拿來開發軟體，那我們會推薦這個散布版。"

#. translators: We try to be friendly and inviting here. The term "get a CD" does not have to be translated exactly.
#: docroot/lib/views/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:135
msgid "Now get a CD and try or install your distribution!"
msgstr "現在就取得一張光碟，並體驗一下或是直接安裝你的散布版吧！"

#. translators: This is the catcher-phrase for the Windows page. Exact translation is not required, the goal is to attract attention and set the tone of the page.
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:21
msgid "Windows and Office work fine &mdash; Why worry about it?"
msgstr "Windows 和 Office 用得好好的 &mdash; 有什麼好擔心的？"

#. translators: You may add emphasis ('em' tags) around the word 'licensed' if you wish
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:29
msgid "A legal copy of Windows is expensive, but what do you get? Windows and Office are licensed, not sold."
msgstr "一份合法的正版 Windows 那麼昂貴，但是你得到了什麼呢？Windows 和 Office 都只是授權使用而已，而非出售給你。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:30
msgid "By using these products, we have to agree to <strong>a number of harsh restrictions</strong>. For most Windows licenses, you can't keep the software when you change the hardware. You sometimes can't even give your software away. Who can run the software? On which computer? What can you do with it? The list of restrictions is long and some items are outrageous."
msgstr "要使用這些產品，我們必需同意<strong>一系列的嚴格限制</strong>。對大多數的 Windows 授權來說，你不能在更換硬體的的時候還保留軟體。有的時候，你甚至不能送出你購買的軟體。誰可以執行軟體？在哪一臺電腦上？你可以拿它來做什麼？那張滿是限制的清單又臭又長，有些條款甚至到了不可理喻的程度。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:36
msgid "Software should come without locks in it."
msgstr "軟體不應該附帶任何枷鎖。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:37
msgid "Why are Office documents difficult to export? Why are the formats continually changing? Why can you not even uninstall some programs? It might be that if you look for choice, Microsoft products aren't for you."
msgstr "為什麼 Office 的文件難以匯出呢？為什麼這些檔案格式不斷更動呢？為什麼你難以解除安裝某些程式？如果你在尋找其他選擇，那麼 Microsoft 的產品可能不適合你。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:43
msgid "The source codes of Windows and Office are hidden, so, <strong>no one is allowed to understand</strong> how these programs work."
msgstr "Windows 和 Office 的源始程式碼被隱藏起來，所以，<strong>沒有人可以去瞭解</strong>這些程式是如何運作的。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:44
msgid "If you can't get a right to inspect source code (the human-readable inner workings of a program), you can't have someone correct flaws or evaluate how your privacy is protected for you."
msgstr "如果你不能獲得檢視源始程式碼（一種人類可讀的程式內部運作機制）的權利，你就不能請專家來修補漏洞或是檢視你的隱私權是否受到保護。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:45
msgid "And guess what? On software that comes with source code, viruses and spyware aren't effective, and security isn't bought on extra. The antivirus software industry, in which Microsoft is now a significant player, prefers you to use Windows."
msgstr "然後你猜怎麼樣？在開放源始碼的軟體上，病毒和間諜軟體都難以作用！所以你不需要另外花錢就能保有安全。防毒軟體產業特別希望你使用 Windows，因為 Microsoft 在這產業中扮演了相當重要的角色。"

#. translators: In your language, you might not need to make the distinction between price and freedom. Please do however express that price does not matter, in this sentence.
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:53
msgid "A free society requires free software. Think of &quot;free&quot; as in freedom, not price: the freedoms to inspect, learn from, modify the software you use."
msgstr "一個自由的社會需要自由的軟體。想一下所謂言論自由的那種「自由」：你可以自由的探索、學習、甚至是修改你正在使用的軟體。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:54
msgid "Computers are used to share ideas, culture and information. Without these freedoms over software, we risk losing control over what we share."
msgstr "電腦是用來分享想法、文化和資訊的途徑。如果沒有了以上所說的那些自由，我們則將很有可能失去這些分享的掌控權。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:55
msgid "This is happening today. From plain annoying technologies such as Digital Restrictions Management (<strong>DRM</strong>) to downright frightening ones like <strong>Trusted Computing</strong>, everyone's ability to participate in culture is threatened."
msgstr "而這一切現在正在發生。從一些惱人的科技，如「數位限制管理」(<strong>DRM</strong>)，到十分嚇人的<strong>信任式運算</strong>，每個人參與文化的權利都正被它們所威脅。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:56
msgid "If you have to give up your freedoms to use software, maybe you should not be happy with it."
msgstr "如果你必須放棄自由才能使用這些軟體，我想也許你會不開心了吧。"

#. translators: This is the conclusion of the article.
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:65
#, php-format
msgid "Many people find that Windows, an otherwise decent piece of software, <strong>withdraws so many rights</strong> from them, that it is not worth them using it. macOS is <a href=\"%s#mac_freedom\">not much better</a>, either."
msgstr "許多人都發現，Windows 雖然是很優秀的作業系統，<strong>但它剝奪了使用者太多的權利</strong>，所以不值得使用。macOS 也<a href=\"%s#mac_freedom\">沒有比較好</a>。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.php:66
#, php-format
msgid "If you find <a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html\" title=\"what is freedom in software?\" rel=\"external\">free software</a> attractive, you might want to <a href=\"%s\" title=\"make the switch to GNU/Linux today!\">give GNU/Linux a try</a>."
msgstr "如果您發現<a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html\" title=\"what is freedom in software?\" rel=\"external\">自由軟體</a>對您來說有吸引力，您可能會想要<a href=\"%s\" title=\"make the switch to GNU/Linux today!\">試試看 GNU/Linux</a>。"

#. translators: This is the very first sentence every visitor is going to read. Please pay great attention to making it sound great, we only have one try! =)
#: docroot/lib/views/home.php:18
msgid "GNU/Linux is an alternative to Microsoft Windows and macOS. It is easy to use and gives more freedom to users. Anyone can install it: GNU/Linux is free as in freedom, and often available free of charge."
msgstr "GNU/Linux 是 Microsoft Windows 和 macOS 作業系統之外的另一種選擇。它簡單易用、給使用者更多的自由。任何人都能安裝：因為 GNU/Linux 是自由軟體，英文為 free software，這裡的 free 是「自由 (freedom)」而非「免費 (free)」，在通常情況下都能無償取得。"

#: docroot/lib/views/home.php:27
msgid "Learn more about the free operating system"
msgstr "深入瞭解自由的作業系統"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:19
msgid "Microsoft works hard to make sure their users stay locked into their products."
msgstr "微軟為了確保用戶在他們產品的嚴格控制下而做出了巨大的努力。"

#. translators: This is a quote from Bill Gates at the start of the article.
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:26
msgid "About 3 million computers get sold every year in China, but people don't pay for the software."
msgstr "中國每年賣出300萬臺電腦，但人們卻不願為軟體付錢。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:27
msgid "Someday they will, though. As long as they are going to steal it [sic], we want them to steal ours. They'll get sort of addicted, and then we'll somehow figure out how to collect sometime in the next decade."
msgstr "總有一天他們會付錢的。只要他們想要盜版 [sic] ，我們就希望他們盜的是我們的軟體。他們會開始上癮，然後我們就能在十年後想出把錢收回的辦法。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:28
msgid "1998 interview"
msgstr "1998年訪談"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:32
msgid "Poor support for open standards"
msgstr "對開放標準的支援很差"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:33
msgid "There exist open file formats and protocols, which are standards to store and carry many types of information, respectively. They are openly specified: they can be read by anyone on any computer, now and in the future. Proprietary programs, however, rarely support them."
msgstr "我們有開放的檔案格式和協定，各自有存放和傳遞各種資訊類型的標準。規格書也都公開透明：因此不管現在和未來都可以被任何人在任何電腦上讀取。可惜的是，專有軟體卻很少願意支援它們。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:34
msgid "<strong>For a long time Microsoft Office only had support for Microsoft formats</strong>. There are many ways to write work documents, but Microsoft Office users were bound to Microsoft Office files. People who opted without expensive Microsoft products cannot write and read <code>.doc</code> files very reliably."
msgstr "<strong>有很長的一段時間，微軟的 Office 只支援微軟自己的檔案格式</strong>。編寫一份工作文件有許許多多的方式，可是 Office 用戶已經緊緊地被微軟 Office 文件格式綁架了。人們如果不願意為微軟昂貴的產品付費，就無法可靠地讀寫 <code>.doc</code> 文件。"

#. translators: Please use link to localized Wikipedia article in place of ODF
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:37
msgid "There are of course other ways of writing and exchanging office files, the most well-known being <a href=\"http://www.opendocumentformat.org/\" rel=\"external\">the OpenDocument Format</a>. But Microsoft isn't keen on letting Office users exchange files anyone can read and edit. As of Microsoft Office 2007 SP2, Microsoft finally added support for the ODF format after being pushed by the European Commission."
msgstr "編寫以及交換文件檔案的方式也有有很多很多種，其中最知名的是<a href=\"http://www.opendocumentformat.org/\" rel=\"external\">開放文件格式，ODF</a>。但微軟並不想讓 Office 的用戶使用任何人都可以讀取及編輯的檔案格式。直到微軟 Office 2007 SP2 起，微軟才因為來自歐盟的壓力，終於加入對 ODF 格式的支援。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:41
msgid "Standards that change all the time"
msgstr "標準總是在改"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:42
msgid "Sticking to Microsoft standards is not an easy job &ndash; unless you can afford to upgrade very often. Ever tried to work on the same <code>.doc</code> file with both an Office 95 and an Office 97 computer? You'll know what we mean."
msgstr "緊跟微軟的標準持續升級並不是一件簡單的工作 &ndash; 除非你能付得起經常升級的費用。你曾經歷過在 Office 95 和 Office 97 間交換 <code>.doc</code> 文件的痛苦嗎？如果有，你大概能理解我在說什麼。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:43
msgid "Microsoft owns the Office file formats: <strong>they change them with every new Office version</strong> and have no obligation to keep them backwards-compatible. Saved your presentation as a <code>.ppt</code> file? If you give up using Microsoft Office next year, you'll have to rely on other communities to reverse-engineer the format, to be able to access and modify your own work."
msgstr "微軟擁有自己的 Office 檔案格式：<strong>他們在每次 Office 新版本中都會動手修改</strong>，而且並不會保持向前的相容性。如果你將之前已簡報儲存為<code>.ppt</code>檔，但明年你考慮放棄微軟 Office 之時，你就不得不依靠其他對這種文件格式作逆向工程的社群，如此才能存取、並修改你的文件。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:47
msgid "Default programs you can't uninstall"
msgstr "預設軟體不能移除"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:48
msgid "Don't want Windows Media Player on your computer? Don't use Internet Explorer anymore? <strong>You can't uninstall these programs</strong>. They previously worked on a standalone basis, but have been intrinsically linked with Windows &ndash; so they come in with every PC and no one can get rid of them."
msgstr "你不希望在你的電腦上有 Windows Media Player 嗎？根本不想再用 Internet Explorer？<strong>很抱歉你沒有辦法移除這些程式</strong>。它們曾經是獨立的程式，但是現在已經被緊緊地綁到 Windows 內部之中 &ndash; 它們出現在幾乎每一臺電腦上，永遠無法擺脫。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:52
msgid "Monopolistic practices"
msgstr "壟斷手法"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:53
msgid "Microsoft has a tight control over <abbr title=\"Original Equipment Manufacturer\">OEM</abbr>s (computer manufacturers) who ship their computers with Windows installed."
msgstr "微軟緊緊控制住 <abbr title=\"Original Equipment Manufacturer，原始設備製造商\">OEM</abbr> 廠商（電腦製造商），讓他們在每一臺電腦上安裝 Windows 作業系統。"

#. translators: if you cannot find localized homepages, please leave the URLs as such
#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:56
msgid "This means that no program competing with Microsoft products, be it <a href=\"https://www.videolan.org/vlc/\" rel=\"external\">multimedia player</a>, <a href=\"https://www.getfirefox.com/\" rel=\"external\">web browser</a>, <a href=\"https://www.libreoffice.org/\" rel=\"external\">office suite</a>, <a href=\"https://www.pidgin.im/\" rel=\"external\">instant messaging program</a> or other, will come pre-installed on most computers you can buy."
msgstr "這意味著沒有軟體能和微軟的產品競爭，不論是<a href=\"https://www.videolan.org/vlc/\" rel=\"external\">多媒體播放器</a>、<a href=\"https://www.getfirefox.com/\" rel=\"external\">網頁瀏覽器</a>、<a href=\"https://www.libreoffice.org/\" rel=\"external\">辦公套裝軟體</a>、<a href=\"https://www.pidgin.im/\" rel=\"external\">即時通訊軟體</a>、或是其他的軟體等，基本上絕大多數你買得到的電腦都已經預裝微軟的產品。"

#: docroot/lib/views/windows.what_about_choice.php:57
msgid "It is a good thing to propose a wide range of software and services like Microsoft do; however, designing and combining them to shut users from non-Microsoft peers is unethical. It's not technically hard to adopt more open formats. But it means your customers are <em>free to choose what they do with their work</em> &ndash; Microsoft isn't there yet."
msgstr "像微軟一樣提供種類繁多的軟體和服務是一件很好的事情；然而，把它們設計成結合起來以阻擋其他非微軟的用戶卻是一個不道德的行為。採用更多的開放格式就技術上來說並非難題，但是這會導致更多的消費者獲得更多<em>選擇自己想要、需要什麼的自由</em> &ndash; 而這並非微軟所樂見的。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:18
msgid "Selected reading on the Internet."
msgstr "閱讀其他精選的網路文章。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:23
msgid "Questions and help"
msgstr "問題與說明"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:27
msgid "<strong>Unix & Linux Stack Exchange</strong> is a question and answer site for users of GNU/Linux. This site is all about getting answers."
msgstr "<strong>Unix & Linux Stack Exchange</strong> 是 GNU/Linux 使用者的問題與回答的網頁。這個網頁完全是取得答案的好地方。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:30
msgid "<strong>Ask Fedora</strong> is a forum for Fedora users. Here you can speak to the community to get help with installing, using, customizing, and upgrading a system running Fedora."
msgstr "<strong>Ask Fedora</strong> 是 Fedora 使用者的論壇。在這裡，您可以與社群討論並取得關於安裝、使用、自訂與升級執行 Fedora 系統的說明。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:34
msgid "<strong>Ask Ubuntu</strong> is a question and answer site for Ubuntu users. Even for users of different distributions of GNU/Linux this can be a helpful resource for finding answers."
msgstr "<strong>Ask Ubuntu</strong> 是一個 Ubuntu 使用者的問題與回答的網站。即便對其他 GNU/Linux 散佈版的使用者來說也是很有用的尋找答案的地方。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:39
msgid "Learn and read more"
msgstr "閱讀並瞭解更多"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:43
msgid "A short, entertaining way to clarify thoughts about free, libre, \"open-source\" software."
msgstr "用一種言簡意賅又有趣的方式來闡明自由、「開放源碼」軟體的中心思想。"

#: docroot/lib/views/more.php:47
msgid "The Free Software Foundation defends and advocates the very concept of <a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html\" rel=\"external\">free software</a> that gave birth to GNU/Linux."
msgstr "自由軟體基金會捍衛並倡導因為有<a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html\" rel=\"external\">自由軟體</a>才誕生了 GNU/Linux 的觀念。"

